              <div class="example" id="passthrough">
                  <div class="col-xs-11 col-sm-11 col-md-11">
                      <h2><a href="./">Ballerina by Example</a>: Passthrough</h2>
                  </div>
                  <div class="col-xs-1 col-sm-1 col-md-1">
                      <a href="./" class="cBackButton"><img src="http://b.content.wso2.com/sites/all/ballerina/backbutton.svg"/></a>
                  </div>
                  <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12 col-md-12">

                      

                      <table>
                          
                          <tr>
                              <td class="docs">
                                  <p>The passthrough sample exhibits the process of HTTP client connector. It returns the response of a backend service.</p>

                              </td>
                              <td class="code leading">
                                  
                                  <div class="highlight"><pre><span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nx">ballerina</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">net</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">http</span><span class="p">;</span>
</pre></div>

                              </td>
                          </tr>
                          
                          <tr>
                              <td class="docs">
                                  <p>A service can be invoke by the name itself when basePath is not stated specifically. In this sample service basepath is &lsquo;/passthrough&rsquo;.</p>

                              </td>
                              <td class="code leading">
                                  
                                  <div class="highlight"><pre><span class="kd">service</span><span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nx">http</span><span class="p">&gt;</span> <span class="nx">passthrough</span> <span class="p">{</span>
</pre></div>

                              </td>
                          </tr>
                          
                          <tr>
                              <td class="docs">
                                  <p>GET{} annotation adds the HTTP method.</p>

                              </td>
                              <td class="code leading">
                                  
                                  <div class="highlight"><pre><span class="nd">@http:GET{</span><span class="p">}</span>
<span class="nd">@http:Path {</span><span class="nx">value</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="s">&quot;/&quot;</span><span class="p">}</span>
<span class="kd">resource</span> <span class="nx">passthrough</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="kt">message</span> <span class="nx">m</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="p">{</span>
</pre></div>

                              </td>
                          </tr>
                          
                          <tr>
                              <td class="docs">
                                  <p>While creating an End point, the host should be given as a parameter.</p>

                              </td>
                              <td class="code leading">
                                  
                                  <div class="highlight"><pre>  <span class="nx">http</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="nx">ClientConnector</span> <span class="nx">endPoint</span> <span class="p">=</span> <span class="nx">create</span> 
    	<span class="nx">http</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="nx">ClientConnector</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s">&quot;http://samples.openweathermap.org&quot;</span><span class="p">);</span>
</pre></div>

                              </td>
                          </tr>
                          
                          <tr>
                              <td class="docs">
                                  <p>Action get() returns the response from backend service. It includes endPoint, resource path and message as parameters.</p>

                              </td>
                              <td class="code leading">
                                  
                                  <div class="highlight"><pre>  <span class="kt">message</span> <span class="nx">response</span> <span class="p">=</span> <span class="nx">http</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="nx">ClientConnector</span>
            <span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">get</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nx">endPoint</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s">&quot;/data/2.5/weather?lat=35&amp;lon=139&amp;appid=b1b1&quot;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="nx">m</span><span class="p">);</span>
  <span class="nx">reply</span> <span class="nx">response</span><span class="p">;</span>
</pre></div>

                              </td>
                          </tr>
                          
                          <tr>
                              <td class="docs">
                                  
                              </td>
                              <td class="code">
                                  
                                  <div class="highlight"><pre> <span class="p">}</span>
    
<span class="p">}</span>
</pre></div>

                              </td>
                          </tr>
                          
                      </table>


                      

                      <table>
                          
                          <tr>
                              <td class="docs">
                                  <p>To run the service, put the code in <code>passthrough.bal</code>
 and use <code>$BALLERINA_HOME/bin</code>.</p>

                              </td>
                              <td class="code leading">
                                  
                                  <div class="highlight"><pre><span class="gp">$</span> ballerina run service passthrough.bal
</pre></div>

                              </td>
                          </tr>
                          
                          <tr>
                              <td class="docs">
                                  <p>Service deployment:</p>

                              </td>
                              <td class="code">
                                  
                                  <div class="highlight"><pre><span class="go">ballerina: deploying service(s) in &#39;passthrough.bal&#39;</span>
<span class="go">ballerina: started server connector http-9090</span>
</pre></div>

                              </td>
                          </tr>
                          
                      </table>


                      

                      <table>
                          
                          <tr>
                              <td class="docs">
                                  <p>To invoke the service, use following client.</p>

                              </td>
                              <td class="code leading">
                                  
                                  <div class="highlight"><pre><span class="gp">$</span> curl -v http://localhost:9090/passthrough
</pre></div>

                              </td>
                          </tr>
                          
                          <tr>
                              <td class="docs">
                                  <p>Server response:</p>

                              </td>
